# Birthday Tracker Web App

Welcome to the "Birthday Tracker" web application! This project is developed using Flask, Python, HTML, CSS, and SQL. It allows you to add and delete birthdays and generates a table to display them.

![Website Screenshot](imageshow.png)

## How to Run the Web Application

To run the web application locally on your machine, follow these steps:

1. **Clone the Repository:** 
If you haven't already, clone this repository to your local machine using the following command:
  ```bash
  git clone https://github.com/rebeca-bc/cs50.git
2. **Navigate to the "birthdays" Folder:**
Change your working directory to the "birthdays" folder using the cd command:
  bash
3. **Copy code**
  cd cs50/birthdays
4. **Install Dependencies:**
If you haven't installed the required dependencies, use pip to install them:
  bash
  Copy code
  pip install -r requirements.txt
  Set Up the Database: Initialize the database by running the following command:
  bash
  Copy code
  flask db init
5. **Migrate and Upgrade the Database:** 
Apply the initial migration and upgrade the database schema:
  bash
  Copy code
  flask db migrate
  flask db upgrade
6. **Run the Application:** 
Start the Flask web server by running the following command:
  bash
  Copy code
  flask run
  The application will be available at http://127.0.0.1:5000/ in your web browser.

7. Interact with the Application: You can now interact with the web application, add birthdays, delete them, and explore the birthday table.
